Great Sea Battles
Spring Books | 1963 | ISBN: N/A | English | 312 pages | PDF | 60.7 MB


Four centuries of great courage and magnificent daring, of ships in victory and defeat on the oceans of the world - this is the romantic subject of Great Sea Battles. From slave galleys and sailing ships to iron-clads and aircraft carriers, here is a rich canvas of naval history stamped with the personalities of the great commanders - Drake, Tromp, Howe, Nelson, Graf von Spec, and many others
